Introduction

This is our R Notebook, showing the steps we took to complete Project 5 for CS 329E. This notebook includes step-by-step instructions on how to reproduce our project. To obtain our data, we used data.world.

R Configuration

Below we display our sessionInfo().

sessionInfo(package=NULL)

Data Description

All data were obtained through esapubs.org. The dataset, Pantheria, contains 100740 lines of biological data for extant and recently extinct mammalian species and was collect over a span of three years. All data came as one textfile, which we edited using Microsoft Excel.

Shiny Visualization and Published Application

Description: A static .png of the Shiny application, as well as a link to the live published version. Crosstab 1 sums up the shipping costs by segment and state. The data is filtered on Country = United States and dislays the IN of Two Highest Shipping Segments. Crosstab 2 breaks down the sum of sales by ship mode and state. The color highlights KPI - Sales per person Low to High. Again, the data is filtered on Country = United States and IN for Two Least Used Shipping Mode. Lastly, Crosstab 3 covers sum of sales by sub-category and country. KPI reflects the profit to sales ratio low to high. The data is filtered on IN for Five Highest Sub-Categories. Published Link: https://frannyfang.shinyapps.io/crosstab2/ https://frannyfang.shinyapps.io/Crosstab3/
